NETWORK SCAN PROJECT REPORT

1. Introduction
   This project was performed to understand local network scanning, open port identification, service detection, and packet analysis using Nmap and Wireshark.

2. Tools Used

* Kali Linux
* Nmap
* Wireshark
* VMware

3. Commands Used
   sudo nmap -sS 192.168.93.0/24

sudo nmap -sV -O 192.168.93.0/24

4. Findings

* Multiple active hosts were detected in the local network.
* Windows and Linux operating systems were identified.
* Open ports such as 80 and 53 were discovered.
* Apache HTTP service was detected on port 80.
* Wireshark successfully captured TCP SYN, ACK, ARP, and retransmission packets.

5. Security Risks

* Open HTTP service may expose unencrypted traffic.
* SMB and RPC services may increase attack surface.
* Open ports can potentially be exploited if not secured.

6. Conclusion
   This project helped in understanding network reconnaissance, TCP SYN scanning, service enumeration, operating system detection, and packet capture analysis using Wireshark.
